7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Fellow and Wrike AI share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Collaboration. Where Fellow pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Notes, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Fellow holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Wrike AI scores 7/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Fellow and Wrike AI offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Fellow's free tier and Wrike AI's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
