b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Fellow is best suited for managers, meeting heavy teams, leadership, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Wrike AI, meanwhile, shines for enterprise teams, professional services, marketing ops, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Fellow describes itself as \"AI meeting management platform for agendas, notes, and action items.\" Wrike AI, established in 2006, positions itself as \"Enterprise work management platform with AI-powered project intelligence.\" With 11 years between them, Wrike AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Fellow offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Fellow** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 9), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Wrike AI is a poor choice — far from it. Wrike AI excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise teams and professional services.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent meeting note templates, go with Fellow. If strong enterprise features and security matters more to you, Wrike AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
